#==========
# Abstract:
#==========

Title:
  Continuous Wavelet Dynamic Time Warping for unbalanced global mapping of two signals


Author:
  Renmin Han,
  Yu Li,
  Sheng Wang,
  Xin Gao


Contact email:
  realbigws@gmail.com
  xin.gao@kaust.edu.sa


#=========
# Install:
#=========

./install.sh


#=======
# Usage:
#=======

#---- type ----#
./cwDTW -h


#---- usage ---#
required:
[-i SHORT SIGNAL][-p LONG SIGNAL][-o OUTPUT]
optional:
([-r NEIGHBOUR RADIUS])([-l LEVEL])([-s SCALE])([-m mode])([-M dp_mode])
([-v verbose])([-t test])([-c len_check])
-------------------------------------------------------------
**** required: ******
SHORT SIGNALE: (reference) sequence signal from ATCG...;
LONG SIGNAL:   (nanopore) raw electrical current signal;
OUTPUT:   signal alignment result; if not specified, then no output be generated;
**** key parameters: ******
NEIGHBOUR RADIUS: warp search radius (default 50);
LEVEL:    sampling level in continous wavelet (default 2);
SCALE:    base scale in continous wavelet (default sqrt(2));
**** vice parameters: ******
mode:     cDTW radius mode. 0 for 'set' and 1 for 'adapt' (default 0)
dp_mode:  final cDTW mode. 0 for 'normal' and 1 for 'restrict' (default 0)
verbose:  0 for NO screenout message, 1 for screenout (default 0);
test:     test mode. 0 for not_use; 1 for equal_ave; 2 for peak_ave (default 0)
check:    0 for NO check length; 1 for swap shorter signal to first (default 0)



#=========
# Example:
#=========

#-> 1. generate genome signal from DNA sequence via pore model.
./seq2sig -i example/002a08b9-0248-4929-9759-2d5c0942076d.fasta -o 002a08b9-0248-4929-9759-2d5c0942076d.seqsig

#-> 2. perform alignment between nanopore signal and genome signal
./cwDTW -i example/002a08b9-0248-4929-9759-2d5c0942076d.seqsig -p example/002a08b9-0248-4929-9759-2d5c0942076d.rawsig -o align_out



